## Important Rules

- **Median, not mean.** Small-team velocity numbers are dominated by single outliers.
- **Throughput is not productivity.** State this on the report. Don't let a number drive a bad decision.
- **Inflection points are prompts.** The skill cannot know why a curve bent. It names candidates.
- **Per-contributor stats are signal, not score.** State this prominently. Performance management does not happen in this report.
- **Bots are noise.** Filter them. Always.
- **Idempotent.** Re-running the same week produces the same numbers. No append-only side effects beyond intel.jsonl.
- **Velocity is one lens.** Pair with `/retro`, `/qa`, customer-outcomes data.
